Police hold grave concerns for a  teenage girl who has been missing for more than a week.

Taylor Almond, 16, was last seen at her Dudley home, a southern coastal suburb of Newcastle in New South Wales, at about 1.00pm on Sunday October 12. 

Police from Lake Macquarie Local Area Command have revealed new information on her possible whereabouts. 

